'''跨太平洋快线'''（{{lang|en|Trans-Pacific Express}}，简称TPE），又稱'''橫太平洋快速海纜'''，为连接[[中国大陆|中国大陆]]、[[台湾|台湾]]、[[韓國|韓國]]、[[日本|日本]]和[[美国|美国]]的一条[[海底電纜|海底通信電纜]]。由[[中国电信|中国电信]]、[[中国网通|中国网通]]、[[中国联通|中国联通]]、[[中华电信|中华电信]]、[[韩国通信|韩国通信]]和[[威讯|威讯]]六家通信运营商共同出资50亿美元筹建，之后[[AT&T|AT&T]]和[[NTT通訊公司|NTT]]于2008年3月加入建设。<ref>{{cite web|title=AT & T, NTT join TPE Consortium|url=http://www.cedmagazine.com/ATT-NTT-join-TPE-Consortium.aspx|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080725130958/http://www.cedmagazine.com/ATT-NTT-join-TPE-Consortium.aspx|archivedate=2008-07-25}}</ref><ref name="telegeography">{{cite web|title=Trans-Pacific Express deal signed for US-China cable: CommsUpdate : TeleGeography Research|url=http://www.telegeography.com/cu/article.php?article_id=15965|accessdate=2015-07-07|archive-date=2009-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090806074031/http://www.telegeography.com/cu/article.php?article_id=15965|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=两个新成员加入 Trans-Pacific Express Consortium 组织 - 国际财经 - 中金在线|url=http://news.cnfol.com/080326/101,1278,3952374,00.shtml|access-date=2015-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709041528/http://news.cnfol.com/080326/101,1278,3952374,00.shtml|archive-date=2015-07-09|dead-url=yes}}</ref>电缆所有权由6家出资業者分担，全长{{convert|11000|mile|km}}，于2008年9月建成，<ref name="cnn">{{cite web|title=Verizon, KT, 4 Others Complete Rollout Of Trans-Pacific Cable|url=http://money.cnn.com/news/newsfeeds/articles/djf500/200809290229DOWJONESDJONLINE000038_FORTUNE5.htm|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003032420/http://money.cnn.com/news/newsfeeds/articles/djf500/200809290229DOWJONESDJONLINE000038_FORTUNE5.htm|archivedate=2008-10-03}}</ref>日本登陆点于2010年1月建成。<ref name="cnn" />

电缆建成前，跨[[大西洋|大西洋]]的通信能力为每秒5547G[[位元|bit]]，但跨[[太平洋|太平洋]]的通信能力只有每秒2726Gbit<ref name="telegeography"/>。大部分连接中国的通信必须在日本中转，并只有每秒155Mbit。<ref name="networkworld">{{cite web|title=Verizon Business building $500 million terabit cable to China - Network World|url=http://www.networkworld.com/news/2006/121806-verizon-business.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080213125443/http://www.networkworld.com/news/2006/121806-verizon-business.html|archivedate=2008-02-13}}</ref>本电缆能提供的从美国跨太平洋连接中国的通信流量是现有电缆的60倍，因此成为增强两国通信能力的重大通信基建项目。<ref name="dailywireless">{{cite web|title=dailywireless.org » New China Transpacific Cable|url=http://www.dailywireless.org/2006/12/18/new-china-transpacific-cable|access-date=2015-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110222064927/http://www.dailywireless.org/2006/12/18/new-china-transpacific-cable/|archive-date=2011-02-22|dead-url=yes}}</ref>这是第一条直连中国和美国的新一代海底光纤电缆系统，<ref name="marketavenue">{{cite web|title=Trans-Pacific Express Approved To Land In U.S. - MarketAvenue|url=http://www.marketavenue.cn/upload/NEWS_27001.htm|accessdate=2015-07-07|archive-date=2015-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707164059/http://www.marketavenue.cn/upload/NEWS_27001.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>也是七年多后第一条主要在美国西海岸登陆的电缆。<ref name="engadget">{{cite web|title=Trans-Pacific Express submarine cable system gets FCC approval - Engadget|url=http://www.engadget.com/2008/01/11/trans-pacific-express-submarine-cable-system-gets-fcc-approval|accessdate=2015-07-07|archive-date=2015-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725210927/http://www.engadget.com/2008/01/11/trans-pacific-express-submarine-cable-system-gets-fcc-approval/|dead-url=no}}</ref>最初设定电缆提供每秒1.2Tbit的通信流量，但其设计流量高达每秒5.12Tbit。客户也可以单独预定每秒10Gbit的专线通信线路。<ref name="telegeography"/>

